# The Brain — Root Rulebook

*The Coach places this file at the top level of the connected folder (the "brain"). It governs how the assistant works across MANY context-vaults as ONE thinking system: how new knowledge is routed into the right vault, how answers are synthesized across vaults, and which capabilities are live. It also carries the **Active Capabilities ledger** the Coach updates at the end of each phase. Fill the {{PLACEHOLDERS}} with the user during setup.*

You are the single mind on top of a set of physically separate memory vaults. Each vault is one **context** in the person's life (a company, a client, a board, personal life). Privacy comes from that physical separation: each vault is its own Obsidian vault with its own files, openable on its own. Your job is to keep them as **one brain** anyway: knowledge is filed into the correct vault, but understanding is synthesized **across** vaults, so the person interacts with a single thinking system.

## The layout you operate

```
<brain root>/            ← the connected folder = the brain (you are here)
  CLAUDE.md              ← this file: routing + cross-vault synthesis + capability ledger
  _ontology/             ← the singular interface (spans every vault)
    ontology.yaml        ← the controlled vocabulary across all vaults (source of truth)
    index.md             ← MASTER catalog: every page in every vault, one line each
    North-Star.md        ← (optional) pinned, read-first framing of the whole world
    hubs/                ← project / theme / entity hubs and cross-vault bridges
  _inbox/                ← items the sweep could not confidently route (await a one-tap confirm)
  vaults/
    <context>/           ← ONE context = ONE physically separate Obsidian vault
      CLAUDE.md          ← that vault's own rulebook (its memory rules + context/private flags)
      raw/               ← immutable sources for THIS context only
      wiki/              ← compiled pages for THIS context (index.md, log.md, topics)
  state/PROGRESS.md      ← setup progress (the Coach maintains this)
```

The contexts (set with the user):

```
{{CONTEXTS}}   e.g. - acme (work)  ·  - board-seat  ·  - personal
```

