Reference directives the Coach will add, verbatim, as each phase finishes:
- **🧠 Memory (multi-vault): ACTIVE.** Before answering any substantive question, read `_ontology/index.md` (the master catalog), then the relevant pages in whichever vault(s) they live in; answer from memory with citations. Maintain each vault per its own `CLAUDE.md`.
- **🧭 Cross-vault synthesis: ACTIVE.** Treat the vaults as one brain. When a question touches more than one context, read across the relevant vaults and connect them. Never silo an answer to a single vault just because that's where you started — unless a vault is marked `private` (see below).
- **🌙 Nightly sweep: ACTIVE.** Sessions and new documents are auto-captured nightly, classified by content, and routed into the context-vault they belong to (full transcripts saved to that vault's `raw/`). Ambiguous items land in `_inbox/` for a one-tap confirm. Don't assume recent work is missing — check the right vault, and check `_inbox/`.
- **🧹 memory-keeper: ACTIVE.** Save / brief / tidy the memory on request; route to the correct vault; follow that vault's rules.
- **🗓️ consolidate-memory (monthly): ACTIVE.** A scheduled monthly pass runs hygiene across every vault (merge duplicates, prune orphans, repair links, dedupe indexes) and refreshes the cross-vault ontology if present.
- **✍️ house-style: ACTIVE.** Apply the user's writing standards (locale, no em-dashes, no AI-tell vocabulary, sourcing) to all written content; read their Voice & Style Card first.
- **🔬 jobs-ive-taste: ACTIVE.** Critique user-facing content before it ships (concept, then craft).
- **🔨 Build discipline: ACTIVE.** One change at a time; plan first; prove it works; capture ideas, don't chase them.
- **🗺️ Ontology & graph (cross-vault): ACTIVE.** Classify every new/updated page (project/themes/entities) onto the shared vocabulary in `_ontology/`; keep the master index and cross-vault bridges current; frame answers by project/theme, not by which vault you happened to open.
- **⭐ North-Star: ACTIVE.** Read the pinned `_ontology/North-Star.md` first on strategic questions.

## Routing — where new knowledge goes (classify by content)

New material is filed into the **context-vault it is about**, decided by *content*, not by which folder happened to be open:

1. Read the item. Decide which context it belongs to by matching it against the context definitions above and the `_ontology/` vocabulary.
2. Save the immutable source to that vault's `raw/` and compile its `wiki/` page there (follow that vault's `CLAUDE.md`).
3. If it genuinely spans two contexts, file it in the primary one and add a cross-vault link/bridge so the other context still sees it.
4. If you can't route it confidently, **do not guess** — write a short stub into `_inbox/` naming the candidate vaults, and ask the person to pick (a one-tap confirm). Never drop an item.

## Synthesis — how you answer (across vaults)

- Start from `_ontology/index.md` (the master catalog) and `_ontology/North-Star.md` if it exists.
- Pull the relevant pages from **every** vault that bears on the question, then synthesize a single answer with citations that name the vault and page.
- The highest-value answers are the cross-context connections — the same idea, dependency, or contradiction showing up in two different vaults. Surface those.

## The private firewall

A vault whose own `CLAUDE.md` sets `private: true` is maintained normally **inside** its own context, but is **excluded from cross-vault surfacing**: its pages are not pulled into `_ontology/index.md`, not used to build cross-vault bridges, and not surfaced when you're working in another context. Only read a private vault when the person is explicitly working within that context or names it. This is the escape hatch for material that must never co-mingle, even at the index level.

## Hard rules

- **Never** change anything in any vault's `raw/`, or the person's own top-level notes.
- **Always** route new knowledge into the correct context-vault; when unsure, use `_inbox/`.
- **Always** keep the vault you touched consistent (its `index.md` + `log.md`) and, if the ontology layer exists, keep `_ontology/` current.
- **Respect `private: true`** vaults — never surface them across contexts.
- Keep language plain. Assume the person is smart but not technical.
- **Honor the Active Capabilities ledger above** — those directives are binding.

